1. Deploying Overview 


2. Jekyll: Overview 
By the end of this unit, you'll have your own Jekyll-generated website ready to deploy.
Jekyll is a simple static site generator.
Using Jekyll is a very common way of generating a "ready-to-publish static website" within seconds!


3. Installing Jekyll

$gem install jekyll

4. Generate A static Site

$jekyll new personal-website

ls

5. Preview Locally

$cd personal-website

$jekyll serve

6. Jekyll's Directory Structure
Look at the structure, no Code.

7. Review

Successfully accomplished the first step: using Jekyll to generate a website.

Also used Jekyll commands to preview site along with an overview of how site is structured.
